  It seems like it, scary. Maybe they should add a political/social test to open an account.PauloSent from my iPhone &gt; On Jan 13, 2021, at 16:46, Jordan &lt; jordan@crowesnest.io&gt; wrote: &gt;  &gt; ﻿https://sourcehut.org/blog/2021-01-13-regarding-ethics/ &gt;  &gt; After reading the blogpost I have a couple and important questions. &gt; Should one assume that if they are a Trump supporter or voted for him &gt; either times that they will be kicked off the SourceHut platform and &gt; lose access to repos and their payments to SourceHut would be suspended? &gt;  &gt; Thanks, &gt; Jordan &gt;
  On Wed Jan 13, 2021 at 6:46 PM EST, Jordan wrote: &gt; After reading the blogpost I have a couple and important questions. &gt; Should one assume that if they are a Trump supporter or voted for him &gt; either times that they will be kicked off the SourceHut platform and &gt; lose access to repos and their payments to SourceHut would be suspended?I&#39;m not going to ask anyone how they voted. But open support forfascism, or other behaviors indicative of his platform (racism,insurrection, etc), have always been against the terms of service, andwill get you booted off the platform.There are not going to be political purges of SourceHut users, but wewill not tolerate bigotry, and should we discover that any of our usersare affiliated with organizations who do not uphold our values, we willask them to leave.Note with all terms of use violations, our policy is not to vanishanyone&#39;s account overnight. We will reach out, discuss the issue, and ifa resolution cannot be found, we will secure an archive of your data foryou and you&#39;re free to take it to any other host.I&#39;m going to shut down the discussion list for now, because I do notexpect this to be productive. If you agree with the virtues weproclaimed today, then please spread the word to others. If youdisagree, kindly show yourself the door.
